reviews.review_text: I was so pleased with the service I received from this business. Specially thanks to Karman as she is so friendly and always keep smile on her face. She is extremely knowledgeable and give great recommendations. I would love to come back here again and again.

I was having a bad day and went for a meal. The nicest, most genuine employee started talking to me and really just changed my perspective of my day, Brooklynn should be given a raise or a firm pat on the back as she seems to be the biggest asset the location has to offer.
Such friendly, organized staff. They make me feel so taken care of each and every time we visit

Thank you so much when BMO royaly, w/cheese add bacon, dropped the ball at 11:45!!! I am coming back in the morning with cash!!!! Keep the world off credit!!!!

This location seems very well looked after, very clean and very accurate with your order, from 7-9 it seems very low traffic and you get your order very quickly after about 10 am traffic gets a bit heavier and our order takes 10ish minutes. Staff seem consistent and polite. Overall pleasant experience bringing my children there several days in a row for breakfast. Parking: You can see your vehicle while you eat Wheelchair accessibility: The door has buttons and the stroller i use is much wider than a weelchair, plus plenty of accessibility parking.
The manager here name aman is  so nice cause he was so busy at that time and know my son just want to eat ice cream corn instead of mcslurry, he made it for my son right away! Really appreciate

We went through drive-thru

we were heading out the door carrying a large order when Dan stopped what he was doing and rushed over to take almost all of it and help us with it to our car.    once i got to the car and put what i had in and meet him back to grab the rest of my food he even came and opened the door for me.  to him it may not have been a big deal but to us it was so kind and caring.  thanks dan!  we were thankful for you kindness today! if we are ever in richmond again we will stop by and hope to see him again!
Went there on late Saturday night drive through, Amandeep and his staff were great, delicious food and excellent customer service, highly recommended.

Stopped by the Mcdonalds on Shell Rd on our way home tonight. Ordered a big mac meal. After we had paid Amandeep (The employee serving us) asked us if wed like any sauces, which we would have forgotten to ask for had he not mentioned it. We received our order incredibly fast.  As we were driving away we see Amandeep running toward us sauces in hand, through the parking lot on to the street, waiving us down to deliver the sauces he had promised.  We were blown away by the commitment to exceptional customer service. 5 stars, 6 stars for Amandeep!

Good for a quick meal. Their coffee is good too. I like McDonalds coffee better than the coffee from many other fast food restaurants. McDonalds burgers are good. Especially, the Angus burger. Also, the French fries are the best at McDonalds.  They very uniform in quality. The best part is that McDonalds is clean and have a good quality control of the food they serve.

As far as McDonalds go it is what you expect. I give it 5 stars because Im usually indecisive at the drive thru and they have never been rude even at the end of the night before closing or just graveyard shift in general. Ill come back, like we all do for that late night guilty pleasure.
Dine in allowed, more parking after mini moving.

Don t eat McDonald s often, they ve made a few mistakes over the years which is normal, but it s my go to McDonald s in this area for sure, they re generally really kind and have great service. Keep it up!
